sorted the lemons undergo a meticulous cleaning process they are soaked in large tanks of water to remove any dirt debris or pesticide residue that may be on their surface a gentle water spray and air shipped to wholesale markets lemons are usually packaged in sturdy spacious boxes designed to hold large quantities of fruit while protecting their integrity these boxes are carefully packaged to minimize impact and prevent damage during transit to retail stores lemons are usually packaged in mesh bags to allow good air circulation helping to prolong the shelf life of the fruit these bags also
